  "transcript": [
    {
      "turn": 1,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Hi Aarti, the chicken curry with coconut milk sounds calming. How did it turn out today?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "It was good, but the flavors were a bit off. Maybe I added too much turmeric. I watched a video, but still, some steps I missed, I think."
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Got it, turmeric can be tricky to balance. I get that, even with a video, it's easy to miss a step. What did you adjust next?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Next time, I’ll try using less turmeric and add the coconut milk earlier. Also, I forgot to cook the onions properly—maybe that’s why the taste was flat. Aapke matlb? 😅"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Right, onions are the base, cook them well and the whole dish lifts. Aapke matlb. is 'what do you mean?' in Hindi, right? What's on your mind?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Yes, exactly, \"aapke matlb?\" is \"what do you mean?\" in Hindi. I mix some words sometimes. 😊 Actually, I was just thinking about my NEET PG prep. I feel a bit stuck in some subjects, but today I finally understood a concept in pharmacology—so it’s a good day overall."
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Nice, pharmacology can be tough, you're doing great! What concept clicked today?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "The concept was about beta-blockers and their side effects. I was confused about why they cause bronchoconstriction, but I got it now—because they block beta-2 receptors in the lungs. It felt like a small win! 😊"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Got it, small wins are the best kind. Beta blockers are tricky, but you nailed it. What’s next on your study plan?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Next, I plan to review some clinical medicine cases. I want to connect the theory with real-life scenarios. But after this, I need to take a break—I’ve been studying for hours! Thanks for the chat. 😊"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Take your time, breaks are important, your brain needs it. What’s your go to break activity?\""
    }
  ],
